 ('20', '26', '2', '1', 'fi_fi', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"What I learned from my racist run-in (illustrated)\",\"slug\":\"what-i-learned-from-my-racist-run-in-illustrated\",\"postDate\":1488734597,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"3\":[\"8\"],\"7\":[\"14\"],\"1\":\"<p>Back in July, I had a racist encounter. I say \\u201cencounter\\u201d because when you have skin as light as mine, experiences with racism can feel pretty alien. I don\\u2019t think about the incident often, but certain things &mdash; like aged subway stations or eggs Benedict on waffles &mdash; conjure up the memory. Lately, I\\u2019ve found myself eating a lot of eggs and doing a lot of thinking.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><br><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>My boyfriend and I hop on the subway. The man standing next to us strikes up a conversation. We laugh and chat, enjoying the company of a stranger. Then the man begins to speculate about my white boyfriend\\u2019s background, to which he responds that he\\u2019s British. Then it\\u2019s my turn. \\u201cAnd you, you must be Portuguese or Italian,\\u201d the man says. \\u201cI\\u2019m actually Persian &mdash; Iranian.\\u201d The man turns to my boyfriend. \\u201cBe careful. She\\u2019s going to blow up.\\u201d<br><\\/p>\",\"4\":[\"6\"]}}', '2017-03-05 17:23:17', '2017-03-05 17:23:17', 'f82f742d-8e30-49a7-b43a-4283fb1a58df'),
